NumberUtils.isNumber(String)  is not right when the String is "1.1L"
"1.1L"  is not a Java Number . but NumberUtils.isNumber(String) return true. perhaps change:              if (chars[i] == 'l'                 || chars[i] == 'L') {                 // not allowing L with an exponent                 return foundDigit && !hasExp;             }   to:              if (chars[i] == 'l'                 || chars[i] == 'L') {                 // not allowing L with an exponent                 return foundDigit && !hasExp && !hasDecPoint;             }  